Chilean Stocks: Banco Santander Chile, Cap, Empresas Copec Gain

-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 
2011-03-21T20:42:24Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-21/chilean-stocks-banco-santander-cap-and-sudamericana-de-vapores.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Chilean trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 3:10 p.m. New York time.  The Ipsa index rose 2.8 percent to 4,436.32, its biggest
increase in 21 months.  Banco Santander Chile (BSAN)   gained 2.6 percent to 36.64
pesos, its steepest rise five weeks. Chile’s largest lender
plans to invest $380 million through 2013 to open at least 30
new branches, Chief Executive Officer Claudio Melandri told El
Mercurio.  Cap SA (CAP)   climbed for a third day, rising 2.7 percent
to 22,934 pesos. Chile’s largest steel producer and iron miner
plans to invest $900 million between 2010 and 2013, according to
a presentation posted on the company’s website.  Empresas Copec SA (COPEC)   increased 4 percent to 8,033.7
pesos for the biggest advance in more than six weeks. Chile’s
largest pulp exporter advanced after  Brazil ’s Fibria Celulose
SA, the world’s largest pulp producer, announced price increases
last week, German Guerrero, director of Santiago-based brokerage
MBI Corredores de Bolsa SA, said in a telephone interview today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
